    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "This 996.2 Carrera represents a pinnacle of mechanical preservation. Powered by a 3.6L naturally aspirated flat-six, it features a documented IMS bearing retrofit and a recent rear main seal replacement, mitigating common M96 failure points. The six-speed manual transaxle shifts with surgical precision, paired with a factory-optioned limited-slip differential for superior power delivery. The chassis remains taut, benefiting from refreshed bushings and Bilstein B6 dampers that maintain original geometry and feedback. Borescope inspection confirms zero cylinder bore scoring, and the cooling system has been overhauled with a low-temp thermostat and high-flow water pump. This is a turn-key, enthusiast-grade example with flawless paint depth and a pristine undercarriage.",
